{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17472006","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17472006"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-28T21:54:05+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-28T21:54:05+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"900"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"900","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/900"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.48,0.01,0.01,0.19,0.3]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"900"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"109881"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"900","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/900"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"900"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"92242"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"9"},{"type":"tags","id":"11"},{"type":"tags","id":"24"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"147"},{"type":"tags","id":"1142"},{"type":"tags","id":"4174"},{"type":"tags","id":"4954"},{"type":"tags","id":"4961"},{"type":"tags","id":"4982"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"4992"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11630"},{"type":"tags","id":"11638"},{"type":"tags","id":"11642"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"},{"type":"tags","id":"12908"},{"type":"tags","id":"12916"},{"type":"tags","id":"12919"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"554"},{"type":"contributions","id":"41214"},{"type":"contributions","id":"42172"},{"type":"contributions","id":"43047"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"109881","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/109881"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 10-year-old boy is brought to the Emergency Department by his concerned parents. He has a history of asthma, for which he takes a regular preventer and as-needed reliever. Since developing an upper respiratory tract infection in the last three days, his asthma has worsened though he no longer has a fever or rhinnrhoea. On examination, he can only speak a few words in one breath, is sitting up, hunched forward, and is alert and not cyanosed. His respiratory rate is 48/min, pulse rate 130/min, blood pressure 100/60 mmHg, and oxygen saturation of 91% on room air. He is afebrile. There is a widespread wheeze on auscultation of his chest. A nasopharyngeal and throat swab for Covid-19 yesterday was negative.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following investigations would be most appropriate?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["No investigations required","Monospot test","Repeat throat swab","Chest X-ray","Arterial blood gas"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis child is suffering from an acute asthma exacerbation, likely precipitated by his recent illness. Given his hypoxia, tachycardia, and tachypnoea, this is a severe and potentially life-threatening attack. This is a clinical diagnosis and \u003Cstrong\u003Edoes not require investigation\u003C/strong\u003E.  The likely viral illness is resolving from his symptoms.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA \u003Cstrong\u003EMonospot test\u003C/strong\u003E is useful in the diagnosis of infectious mononucleosis, the clinical presentation of which does not fit the given vignette.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA \u003Cstrong\u003Ethroat swab\u003C/strong\u003E can be used for a bacterial culture or viral PCR, however for this child, his respiratory infection is a less pressing issue than his asthma. In addition, his respiratory infection is likely to be viral and self-resolving, decreasing the utility of a throat swab. Importantly, he was tested for Covid-19 yesterday, which was negative.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA \u003Cstrong\u003Echest X-ray\u003C/strong\u003E is not indicated in severe asthma unless there is a specific indication or suspicion of an alternative diagnosis \u2013 for example, suspicion of pneumonia due to fever or focal auscultation findings.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAn \u003Cstrong\u003Earterial blood gas\u003C/strong\u003E is rarely indicated in paediatric patients and does not typically change the management of a severe asthma attack.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Children with known and documented asthma do not need further investigation if and when they present with an acute episode."],"references":["Ortiz-Alvarez O, Mikrogianakis A; Canadian Paediatric Society, Acute Care Committee. Managing the paediatric patient with an acute asthma exacerbation. Paediatr Child Health. 2012 May;17(5):251-62. doi: 10.1093/pch/17.5.251. PMID: 23633900; PMCID: PMC3381918. Available from: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/23633900/","Castillo JR, Peters SP, Busse WW. Asthma Exacerbations: Pathogenesis, Prevention, and Treatment. J Allergy Clin Immunol Pract. 2017 Jul-Aug;5(4):918-927. doi: 10.1016/j.jaip.2017.05.001. PMID: 28689842; PMCID: PMC5950727. Available from: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/28689842/","Ramsahai JM, Hansbro PM, Wark PAB. Mechanisms and Management of Asthma Exacerbations. Am J Respir Crit Care Med. 2019 Feb 15;199(4):423-432. doi: 10.1164/rccm.201810-1931CI. PMID: 30562041. Available from: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/30562041/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"92242"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"900"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"92242","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/92242"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-07-27T13:05:40+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-07-27T13:06:47+09:30"}